        "answer_count": 1,
        "title": "How can I maintain state when switching between action bar tabs / fragments?",
        "body": "<p>I have a number of fragments attached to the Android action bar as tabs. I can switch between them without problems. However, if one of the fragments has a <code>TextView<\/code> (for example), and I alter the text of that <code>TextView<\/code>, the new text is not kept if I switch to another tab and back. <\/p>\n\n<p>I've tried overriding <code>onSaveInstanceState()<\/code>, but it appears it is not called when I switch tabs, as <code>savedInstanceState<\/code> is <code>null<\/code> every time <code>onActivityCreated()<\/code> is called (i.e. every time that tab is reopened). <\/p>\n\n<p>I looked into altering <code>onPause()<\/code> such that it calls <code>onSaveInstanceState()<\/code>, but <code>onPause()<\/code> doesn't have access to the state bundle, so I don't see how I can do that.<\/p>\n\n<p>What is the best way to keep state in a tab when going back and forth between tabs?<\/p>\n",
        "question_id": 14964565,
        "tags": [
            "java",
            "android"
        ],
        "score": 4,
        "accepted_answer_id": 14965299,
        "is_answered": true,
        "view_count": 2487,
        "last_edit_date": 1361298380
